cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses techniques for improving the performance of a target task through multi-task learning using pre-trained networks and unsupervised learning. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given the focus on improving performance through learning generalized feature representations, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
